Title: Naked Economics: Undressing the Dismal Science
Author: Charles Wheelan
My Review: Enjoyed reading this book. I could visualize the examples given in the book with real world scenarios like why human capital is very important to the GDP of the country. Without investing in the very humans in the form of good education and health care, the country cannot expect them to be productive. Without being productive,how can you improve the GDP of a country. very nice. Also surprised to know that only countries with fewer natural resources really became developed countries and countries with vast amount of natural resources are still not productive.
